What are the most finite resources that you have?
Answer: Your time and energy!

Your time can never be replaced. Time is an investment; Once we give it to causes important to us, relationships of value, pursuits of passion and purpose, we feel a positive return.

However, put your time into people, places, and things that leave you feeling anything 'less than' and you have wasted your time / made a poor investment.

With all of my clients, the most important word in their arsenal is NO.
No is a boundary,
No protects your most precious investments,
No protects your time, energy, purpose & passion.
No protects people that you love.
No is also the most courageous act for so many conditioned to be people pleasers.

Where can you give yourself permission to say No today?

When we have experienced hurt, shame, trauma or just plain old sh*tty days in life, we can become hard. 

We think armour means that we won’t feel pain again. 

So we layer up. 

At first, it maybe even feels good as we can get more done because those pesky unpredictable emotions don’t interrupt us as much.

Life is much better when we are numb - or so it seems. 

We can even trick our trauma into closing itself up nice and tight into a box that we pack away, like our Christmas decorations in January, and push right to the back of the attic. 

The problem is you are not allaying, you are delaying. 

Have you noticed how many people apologise if they become emotional? Their first response is usually ‘I’m sorry’. 

So we lock it away, laugh it off, lead the conversation away. 

What can grow from stark, hard, austere & Barren? 

Very little & there is hardly any pleasure here! 

We need our emotions to flow for creativity, connection, curiosity & chemistry! You know what I am talking about 😉 

How can you give yourself permission / create enough safety & strength to swim in the softness and see what might be possible from here?

What have you learnt this year? ✨

“Courage is the power to let go of the familiar”. Raymond Lindquist. 

Transition can be tough and overwhelming. 

It can feel like we have to grieve, honour and release the old without much certainty or clarity of what is next. 

The transition into the new year, 2023, can be whatever you want it to be. 

Take this transition as an opportunity to reflect on & think about who and what helped you grow in 2022.

The Untethered Soul, which is the book that this beautiful quote comes from is one of the books I recommend & gift the most.

The audio book version arrived in my life a few years ago & accompanied me on one fo the most difficult and beautiful trips to Cap D’Antibes. 

A place drenched in beauty at every turn, but also for me a lot of deeply personal memories were embedded there. 
 Memories that , at the time, were being painfully & painstakingly disentangled with every step I took on yet another lone like around the magnificent coastline. 

It was this book that deconstructed something else on that trip, my ego. 

For the first time, I was able to understand how much of a driving seat I had given over to my ego; in turn, how much I had closed off my heart to receive what had been available to me all along, true freedom. 

I still stumble, I am human. 

I revisit chapters of this book whenever I notice that my ego has slipped back and is playing with the controls & my wild gypsy soul need to be untethered again. I sense it will be quite soon 💫

Putting pressure on yourself to change absolutely everything in your life can feel all too much. 

For me this year I’m choosing to make some slight swaps rather than forcing myself to make unachievable & overwhelmingly large changes.

These swaps, for me, feel necessary and are things & actions that feel manageable and sustainable. 

I always say to my clients that if a ship changes it’s course by just 1 degree it’s destination will be completely different.

So, what swap or marginal change can you make to create the change you want to see or help you move towards the lifestyle you desire?

I often ask clients:
"what would you pay not to do your job / see this person/ do this activity" that is clearly not aligned with themselves or their values and is draining them.

This is when they realise that even the very high earners have a pretty poor hourly rate, especially when they are spending time doing something that they hate.

Remember that your energy is your MOST valuable source of income & expenditure that you have.

Make those investments wisely!

As we reach the half way point of the working week, I would like you to check in with yourself. 

Here is your check-in starting point. A question I ask all my clients:

“How are you feeling?”

But there’s a catch….

You can’t say “Good” “Fine” or “OK”. 

These three are what we so often find ourselves telling others and ourselves in order to band-aid over what we are truly feeling. 

It is almost an automatic response we have to avoid exposing or dealing with any vulnerability or weakness. However, by not addressing our vulnerabilities, we actually make ourselves more vulnerable….

more vulnerable to being sent into the survival zone…which leads to the burnout zone. 

So, start with honestly answering “How are you feeling?” 

and then dig a bit deeper to identify your needs. 

I hope you progress through the rest of your week with a little bit more clarity, positivity and good energy ✨

What does your mind tell you?

Has your mind told you to not take the leap or take the risk? That’s your inner critic.

The climb, rise and grind, pushing through; do all of these sound familiar? We can do any of these for a period of time but not prolonged, if we do, we end up falling off the ever-familiar cliff into burnout.

How many times have you said ' I will slow down / catch up when...' then the weekend, the holiday comes and you crash, most often getting sick? That’s Burnout.

The real secret to sustainable high performance is the antithesis of the constant climb.

You don't see athletes sprinting marathons, they would collapse, but we try to do it, without all of the additional support teams they have in elite sport.

Work in focussed, dedicated sprints. Take regular, quality renewal breaks, and enjoy the steps to success rather than the slide to decline.

Sometimes it is pain that paves the way to freedom. There is no shame in that.

Boundaries have become a buzzword in recent times.

This is a paradox as they are so easy to talk about but yet so many people find them so hard to implement.

We fear the other person may react negatively to our boundary setting. Perhaps we prioritise the need of the other above our own.

Alternatively, do we gain some value from being the person that is always there to give?

Do we fear who we might be and our role if we are no longer readily available in this relationship?

Do we need to be needed?

Here are some ways to introduce boundaries in a more positive sense for all:

- ‘ I know that you can do this without my help, I have seen you do hard things before, you have got this ‘

- ‘ I don’t feel like I can give my focus & energy to this right now & that isn’t best serving you or this issue ‘

- I am spending some time prioritising my passions right now so that I am more able to support yours in the future ‘

Boundaries are barriers that protect relationships of value they are not a rejection.

To love ourselves without condition is the only way to true fulfillment in all our relationships.

But how do we get there? Especially if we feel stuck, tainted, or marked in some way by our past actions.

In systems coaching, there is a technique called ‘lands work’, often used for conflict resolution.

An important shift is sifting through the situation and finding a souvenir, something we can ‘export’ and apply to our lives moving forwards; A memento.

The situation may have been negative, but we can use this to navigate situations in the future more positively.

We pick up trinkets from our travels, and they can transport us back to beautiful beaches in a single glance.

Similarly, so can the treasures of trauma. They can be applied positively to show us how far we have come, how much we have learned, and how many steps have become our own version of air miles on our personal journey.

There is always something of value that we can take out of any situation. 

We never lose if we learn.

Something to hold on to that can give us that glimmer of possibility, to give something meaning to help us shift our pain into purpose.

‘I'll be satisfied if I play along
But the voice inside sings a different song’ Aulii Cravalho (Moana)

We are all our friends with our limitations. Our fears and doubts are fed to us on the daily from our inner critic in some f*cked up form of anti-mantra.

This becomes our cage of comfort, that place we stay, never daring to stray to far into the unknown.

However, every client I see has a flame of something ‘more’ burning inside of them. Whatever you may have called it before it is time to answer it.

Never be afraid of finding out, never be afraid of trying, never be afraid of letting the words fall off your tongue to a friend telling them you are ready to start, allowing that ember of an idea to truly spark.

Then watch that fear melt into focus as you find yourself in flow & like Moana, there is just no telling how far you will go.

Please do not hold any shame if fawning is/was your trauma response.

Burnout has become a word associated with the corporate world, a symptom of stress that can be hard to define.

We need to connect to our purpose, to things that we love to feel alive & fulfilled. But we also need to keep grounded & connected to ourselves from a place of renewal to attain our goals & critically to be able to enjoy them when we have attained them.

Sometimes it can feel easier to keep quiet and not bring a touchy or vulnerable subject up again. This often boils down to fear of rejection. 

So I have 2 tools for you, if you want to have a safe conversation in relationship 

TOOL NO. 1 - HALT
From @sexwithemily Emily Morse (definitely worth a follow) 

If you are….
H - hungry
A - Angry
L - Lonely 
or Tired
…Wait till you’re none of these before having a tricky conversation.
Instead, check in with yourself, manage yourself first and make sure you’re none of these things before having a tricky conversation.

TOOL NO. 2 - I call it First-AID
How to give feedback in any type of relationship:

A - ACTION 
What specifically did they do that you would like to celebrate or change?

I - IMPACT - What was the impact that it had on you or people around you, and them?

D - DO NEXT
What do you want to see more or less of?

In a world where reactions often seem automatic, emotional mastery emerges as the antidote to emotional chaos. It’s about two things: emotional awareness and emotional intelligence. But what truly sets emotional mastery apart is the sacred space between an action and your reaction.

Emotional Awareness:

This is where it all begins. It's about tuning in to your own emotional radar. Recognize your feelings, name them, and understand their intensity. This self-awareness is your compass, guiding your journey toward emotional mastery. But remember, emotions are fleeting - they come, and they go. It's the art of non-attachment that helps you let them pass without consuming you.

The Art of Non-Attachment:

Non-attachment doesn't mean becoming emotionless. It's about not letting emotions dictate your life. Imagine emotions as guests in your house; they visit, they leave. They don't own the place. This mindset shift is the essence of non-attachment. It allows you to acknowledge emotions without being enslaved by them.

Here's the secret sauce to emotional mastery: knowing what you can control and what you can't. You can't control people, external environments, or triggers, but you can absolutely control your reactions. That's where your power lies. When you grasp this distinction, you'll find a newfound sense of freedom and empowerment.

By mastering this space between action and reaction, you regain control of your life. You become the captain of your emotional ship, navigating the turbulent waters of existence with grace and resilience. In this journey, emotional mastery isn't a luxury; it's a necessity. It's the difference between reacting impulsively to life's challenges and responding with wisdom and composure. It's the path to a more fulfilling, balanced, and peaceful existence 💫

Some of the hardest moments we can face and the toughest decisions we need to make are when to stop. 

When is it time to walk away? 

This could apply to a relationship, a friendship, a job, a toxic family member the dynamic that you have felt declining and fought so fiercely to revive . 

However, there can come a time when loving someone or something simply isn’t enough - you are loosing yourself, your peace & your centre. 

This can show up in fairly new connections as well as those with longer roots. The ‘near misses’ hurt more sometimes than those steeped in history. 

You can give and give to someone or something but if they cannot meet your needs there comes a moment when we must take a step back from the situation. 

When something can no longer be revived no matter how pure your intentions, energy or how strong the connection was at the beginning.

The kindest thing for us all can be to stop watering a flower that can no longer bloom.

Shoutout to those of you who have mastered the art of people-pleasing. 

For too long, many of us have contorted ourselves into smaller, more palatable versions of who we truly are - most of the time, all int he pursuit of acceptance and love. 

Life can throw some heavy punches, leaving cards that make us believe we must stay small to be loved. 

It’s a survival instinct, a coping mechanism hones through the challenges of adversity. 

Our old programming believes that safety is in numbers and the only way to stay safe is to stay small, digestible and by not taking up too much space - only then will people find comfort in our company and perhaps love us more. 

Yet, this facade is a disservice to our authentic selves. 

The reality is that genuine love and acceptance should not hinge on our ability to shrink into a mood that puts others at ease. 
 True connections are born when we stand tall, fearlessly embracing every facet of our being, scars and all. 

For the people-pleasers who have become adept at camouflaging their true selves, it’s time to shatter the illusion. 

The real connections we crave are rooted in the courage to be genuine, even if it disrupts the tranquility of someone else’s perception and our (unknowingly) limiting beliefs. 

So, today where can you perhaps step into your fullness, be firm with a boundary, find your true voice, speak up, own your shit. 

Being truly unfiltered to show your raw, authentic self takes courage. 
You might never feel ready but you can always be a little bit courageous ❤️‍🔥

You ‘should’ have that job by now. 
You ‘should’ be earning that amount of money by now.
You ’should’ have it all figured out
You ‘should’ be settled. 
You ‘should’ be a better person.

Sound familiar? 

Ok yes it is technically “blue monday” - and as gloomy as it’s made out to be, as a fun marketing tactic…Let’s use this as an opportunity to rebel against the ‘shoulds’ that are thrown at us 

‘Should’ is the fuel of the inner critic. 
‘Should’ is the voice of society. 
When we feel like we need to be externally validated by other things, it is exhausting and it weighs upon us. 

Notice that you are exhausted but the shoulds and that you have no capacity for what you want to be doing instead. 

Take a moment today to embrace the chaos of life, but on your own terms. 

If you were to weigh up your pile of shoulds and wants, which would be bigger right now?

Changing the balance of this scale doesn’t need to be drastic - but by perhaps taking one ‘should’ off your list, it could lighten and brighten your day.

We need to start creating space for ‘wants’ that set our souls on fire, not ‘shoulds’ that hold us back. 

Choosing your ‘wants’ over the ‘shoulds’ might not solve all your problems, but it’s a rebellious act of self-love that I am absolutely on board for.

If you have been feeling weighed down in the doldrums of continual disappointment then this one is for you. 

By choosing yourself and stepping into the full embodiment of your most authentic upgrade you shed not only the old outdated layers that hid your light but the hangers on that were trying to ensure that you could not be the brightest. 

Feel the lightness of your soul as it is allowed to flow through you unfiltered and watch as the low vibe tribe disappear.

Imagine the energy you can have back for things & people that honour your soul, rather than propping up that one-sided relationship.
Think about the future friendships that you wish to come forwards; who will truly cheer the loudest for you once the fake friends/ frenemies fall away? Those are the keepers.
